{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":498,"text":"So I'd like you to come back with me"},{"time":3157,"text":"just for a few minutes"},{"time":5058,"text":"to a dark night in China,"},{"time":7927,"text":"the night I met my husband."},{"time":10648,"text":"It was a city so long ago that it was still called"},{"time":14091,"text":"Peking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":16204,"text":"So I went to a party."},{"time":18825,"text":"I sat down next to a stout, middle-aged man"},{"time":22208,"text":"with owl glasses and a bow tie,"},{"time":25722,"text":"and he turned out to be a Fulbright scholar,"},{"time":28615,"text":"there in China specifically to study"},{"time":32179,"text":"Sino-Soviet relations."},{"time":34270,"text":"What a gift it was to the eager,"},{"time":36670,"text":"young foreign correspondent that I was then."},{"time":39428,"text":"I'd pump him for information,"},{"time":41436,"text":"I'm mentally scribbling notes"},{"time":43093,"text":"for the stories I plan to write."},{"time":45402,"text":"I talk to him for hours."}]},{"cues":[{"time":47887,"text":"Only months later,"},{"time":51398,"text":"I discover who he really was."},{"time":53772,"text":"He was the China representative"},{"time":56545,"text":"for the American Soybean Association."}]},{"cues":[{"time":60774,"text":"\"I don't understand. Soybeans?"},{"time":64044,"text":"You told me you were a Fulbright scholar.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":66799,"text":"\"Well, how long would you have talked to me"},{"time":68687,"text":"if I told you we're in soybeans?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":70729,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":73210,"text":"I said, \"You jerk.\""},{"time":76502,"text":"Only jerk wasn't the word I used."},{"time":80255,"text":"I said, \"You could've gotten me fired.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":84402,"text":"And he said, \"Let's get married.\""},{"time":87939,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":89226,"text":"\"Travel the world and have lots of kids.\""},{"time":92122,"text":"So we did."}]},{"cues":[{"time":94220,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":96265,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":101507,"text":"And what an alive man Terence Bryan Foley"},{"time":105247,"text":"turned out to be."},{"time":106694,"text":"He was a Chinese scholar"},{"time":108337,"text":"who later, in his 60s,"},{"time":110203,"text":"got a Ph.D. in Chinese history."},{"time":112755,"text":"He spoke six languages,"},{"time":115243,"text":"he played 15 musical instruments,"},{"time":117731,"text":"he was a licensed pilot,"},{"time":119507,"text":"he had once been a San Francisco cable car operator,"},{"time":122678,"text":"he was an expert in swine nutrition,"},{"time":125512,"text":"dairy cattle, Dixieland jazz, film noir,"},{"time":129293,"text":"and we did travel the country, and the world,"},{"time":133477,"text":"and we did have a lot of kids."},{"time":135706,"text":"We followed my job, and it seemed like"},{"time":137448,"text":"there was nothing that we couldn't do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":141015,"text":"So when we found the cancer,"},{"time":144797,"text":"it doesn't seem strange to us at all"},{"time":147362,"text":"that without saying a word to each other,"},{"time":149995,"text":"we believed that,"},{"time":152421,"text":"if we were smart enough"},{"time":154680,"text":"and strong enough and brave enough,"},{"time":159011,"text":"and we worked hard enough,"},{"time":161484,"text":"we could keep him from dying ever."}]},{"cues":[{"time":166762,"text":"And for years, it seemed like we were succeeding."},{"time":170261,"text":"The surgeon emerged from the surgery."},{"time":173140,"text":"What'd he say? He said what surgeons always say:"},{"time":175417,"text":"\"We got it all.\""},{"time":177419,"text":"Then there was a setback when the pathologists"},{"time":180462,"text":"looked at the kidney cancer closely."},{"time":182835,"text":"It turned out to be a rare,"},{"time":184464,"text":"exceedingly aggressive type,"},{"time":186273,"text":"with a diagnosis that was almost universally fatal"},{"time":189355,"text":"in several weeks at most."},{"time":191746,"text":"And yet, he did not die."},{"time":195456,"text":"Mysteriously, he lived on."},{"time":198966,"text":"He coached Little League for our son."},{"time":201050,"text":"He built a playhouse for our daughter."},{"time":203602,"text":"And meanwhile, I'm burying myself in the Internet"},{"time":206676,"text":"looking for specialists."},{"time":208350,"text":"I'm looking for a cure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":210911,"text":"So a year goes by"},{"time":212988,"text":"before the cancer, as cancers do,"},{"time":216194,"text":"reappears,"},{"time":218194,"text":"and with it comes another death sentence,"},{"time":220270,"text":"this time nine months."},{"time":222463,"text":"So we try another treatment, aggressive, nasty."},{"time":226477,"text":"It makes him so sick, he has to quit it,"},{"time":228297,"text":"yet still he lives on."},{"time":231314,"text":"Then another year goes by."},{"time":233210,"text":"Two years go by."},{"time":234760,"text":"More specialists."},{"time":236249,"text":"We take the kids to Italy."},{"time":238169,"text":"We take the kids to Australia."}]},{"cues":[{"time":240638,"text":"And then more years pass,"},{"time":243350,"text":"and the cancer begins to grow."},{"time":245740,"text":"This time, there's new treatments on the horizon."},{"time":248275,"text":"They're exotic. They're experimental."},{"time":250211,"text":"They're going to attack the cancer in new ways."},{"time":253419,"text":"So he enters a clinical trial, and it works."},{"time":257745,"text":"The cancer begins to shrink,"},{"time":259674,"text":"and for the third time,"},{"time":261951,"text":"we've dodged death."}]},{"cues":[{"time":265310,"text":"So now I ask you,"},{"time":268607,"text":"how do I feel"},{"time":270996,"text":"when the time finally comes"},{"time":273510,"text":"and there's another dark night,"},{"time":276016,"text":"sometime between midnight and 2 a.m.?"},{"time":278517,"text":"This time it's on the intensive care ward"},{"time":281491,"text":"when a twentysomething resident"},{"time":283329,"text":"that I've never met before"},{"time":285532,"text":"tells me that Terence is dying,"},{"time":288125,"text":"perhaps tonight."}]},{"cues":[{"time":290324,"text":"So what do I say when he says,"},{"time":293117,"text":"\"What do you want me to do?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":295931,"text":"There's another drug out there."},{"time":297943,"text":"It's newer. It's more powerful."},{"time":299631,"text":"He started it just two weeks ago."},{"time":302200,"text":"Perhaps there's still hope ahead."}]},{"cues":[{"time":305309,"text":"So what do I say?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":307264,"text":"I say, \"Keep him alive if you can.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":310620,"text":"And Terence died six days later."}]},{"cues":[{"time":314135,"text":"So we fought, we struggled, we triumphed."},{"time":318183,"text":"It was an exhilarating fight,"},{"time":319979,"text":"and I'd repeat the fight today"},{"time":321696,"text":"without a moment's hesitation."},{"time":324345,"text":"We fought together, we lived together."},{"time":327296,"text":"It turned what could have been"},{"time":329400,"text":"seven of the grimmest years of our life"},{"time":332134,"text":"into seven of the most glorious."},{"time":335745,"text":"It was also an expensive fight."},{"time":338520,"text":"It was the kind of fight and the kind of choices"},{"time":340481,"text":"that everyone here agrees"},{"time":342115,"text":"pump up the cost of end-of-life care,"},{"time":344520,"text":"and of healthcare for all of us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":346806,"text":"And for me, for us,"},{"time":349888,"text":"we pushed the fight right over the edge,"},{"time":351970,"text":"and I never got the chance to say to him"},{"time":355195,"text":"what I say to him now almost every day:"},{"time":358615,"text":"\"Hey, buddy, it was a hell of a ride.\""},{"time":361692,"text":"We never got the chance to say goodbye."},{"time":364180,"text":"We never thought it was the end."},{"time":366459,"text":"We always had hope."}]},{"cues":[{"time":371638,"text":"So what do we make of all of this?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":375502,"text":"Being a journalist, after Terence died,"},{"time":379080,"text":"I wrote a book, \"The Cost Of Hope.\""},{"time":382369,"text":"I wrote it because I wanted to know"},{"time":384519,"text":"why I did what I did,"},{"time":386205,"text":"why he did what he did,"},{"time":388006,"text":"why everyone around us did what they did."}]},{"cues":[{"time":390561,"text":"And what did I discover?"},{"time":392197,"text":"Well, one of the things I discovered is that"},{"time":393771,"text":"experts think that one answer to"},{"time":396848,"text":"what I did at the end was a piece of paper,"},{"time":399598,"text":"the advance directive,"},{"time":401756,"text":"to help families get past the seemingly irrational choices."},{"time":406096,"text":"Yet I had that piece of paper."},{"time":410210,"text":"We both did."},{"time":412263,"text":"And they were readily available."},{"time":413953,"text":"I had them right at hand."},{"time":415892,"text":"Both of them said the same thing:"},{"time":418251,"text":"Do nothing if there is no further hope."},{"time":422752,"text":"I knew Terence's wishes"},{"time":424972,"text":"as clearly and as surely as I knew my own."}]},{"cues":[{"time":428786,"text":"Yet we never got to no further hope."},{"time":433990,"text":"Even with that clear-cut paper in our hands,"},{"time":436747,"text":"we just kept redefining hope."},{"time":440003,"text":"I believed I could keep him from dying,"},{"time":445295,"text":"and I'd be embarrassed to say that if I hadn't seen"},{"time":448109,"text":"so many people and have talked to so many people"},{"time":450320,"text":"who have felt exactly the same way."},{"time":452994,"text":"Right up until days before his death,"},{"time":456928,"text":"I felt strongly"},{"time":460254,"text":"and powerfully, and, you might say, irrationally,"},{"time":464297,"text":"that I could keep him from dying ever."}]},{"cues":[{"time":469544,"text":"Now, what do the experts call this?"},{"time":472779,"text":"They say it's denial."},{"time":475126,"text":"It's a strong word, isn't it?"},{"time":477317,"text":"Yet I will tell you that denial"},{"time":479714,"text":"isn't even close to a strong enough word"},{"time":484828,"text":"to describe what those of us"},{"time":487474,"text":"facing the death of our loved ones go through."}]},{"cues":[{"time":491112,"text":"And I hear the medical professionals say,"},{"time":493453,"text":"\"Well, we'd like to do such-and-such,"},{"time":495536,"text":"but the family's in denial."},{"time":497987,"text":"The family won't listen to reason."},{"time":500163,"text":"They're in denial."},{"time":502185,"text":"How can they insist on this treatment at the end?"},{"time":504537,"text":"It's so clear, yet they're in denial.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":507841,"text":"Now, I think this maybe isn't"},{"time":509848,"text":"a very useful way of thinking."},{"time":512852,"text":"It's not just families either."},{"time":515130,"text":"The medical professionals too,"},{"time":517255,"text":"you out there, you're in denial too."},{"time":520615,"text":"You want to help. You want to fix."},{"time":523468,"text":"You want to do."},{"time":525294,"text":"You've succeeded in everything you've done,"},{"time":528102,"text":"and having a patient die,"},{"time":530144,"text":"well, that must feel like failure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":533723,"text":"I saw it firsthand."},{"time":535567,"text":"Just days before Terence died,"},{"time":538269,"text":"his oncologist said,"},{"time":540287,"text":"\"Tell Terence that better days are just ahead.\""},{"time":543535,"text":"Days before he died."}]},{"cues":[{"time":545917,"text":"Yet Ira Byock,"},{"time":547350,"text":"the director of palliative medicine at Dartmouth"},{"time":549698,"text":"said, \"You know, the best doctor in the world"},{"time":552629,"text":"has never succeeded in making anyone immortal.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":557237,"text":"So what the experts call \"denial,\" I call \"hope,\""},{"time":563743,"text":"and I'd like to borrow a phrase"},{"time":566077,"text":"from my friends in software design."},{"time":569298,"text":"You just redefine denial and hope,"},{"time":572860,"text":"and it becomes a feature of being human."},{"time":576088,"text":"It's not a bug."},{"time":577949,"text":"It's a feature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":580275,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":583369,"text":"So we need to think more constructively"},{"time":587063,"text":"about this very common, very profound"},{"time":591375,"text":"and very powerful human emotion."},{"time":595331,"text":"It's part of the human condition,"},{"time":597955,"text":"and yet our system and our thinking"},{"time":600132,"text":"isn't built to accommodate it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":603301,"text":"So Terence told me a story on that long-ago night,"},{"time":606356,"text":"and I believed it."},{"time":608261,"text":"Maybe I wanted to believe it."},{"time":611375,"text":"And during Terence's illness, I, we,"},{"time":616704,"text":"we wanted to believe the story"},{"time":618426,"text":"of our fight together too."},{"time":621021,"text":"Giving up the fight -- for that's how it felt,"},{"time":624757,"text":"it felt like giving up --"},{"time":626696,"text":"meant giving up not only his life"},{"time":629413,"text":"but also our story,"},{"time":633120,"text":"our story of us as fighters,"},{"time":635330,"text":"the story of us as invincible,"},{"time":638260,"text":"and for the doctors, the story of themselves"},{"time":640468,"text":"as healers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":643026,"text":"So what do we need?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":645710,"text":"Maybe we don't need a new piece of paper."},{"time":648649,"text":"Maybe we need a new story,"},{"time":651596,"text":"not a story about giving up the fight"},{"time":655605,"text":"or of hopelessness,"},{"time":657876,"text":"but rather a story of victory and triumph,"},{"time":661287,"text":"of a valiant battle and, eventually,"},{"time":666130,"text":"a graceful retreat,"},{"time":668450,"text":"a story that acknowledges"},{"time":671457,"text":"that not even the greatest general defeats every foe,"},{"time":675220,"text":"that no doctor has ever succeeded"},{"time":677841,"text":"in making anyone immortal,"},{"time":680231,"text":"and that no wife, no matter how hard she tried,"},{"time":686297,"text":"has ever stopped even the bravest,"},{"time":690982,"text":"wittiest and most maddeningly lovable husband"},{"time":695031,"text":"from dying when it was his time to go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":699224,"text":"People did mention hospice,"},{"time":701537,"text":"but I wouldn't listen."},{"time":704908,"text":"Hospice was for people who were dying,"},{"time":708833,"text":"and Terence wasn't dying."},{"time":711606,"text":"As a result, he spent just four days in hospice,"},{"time":714516,"text":"which I'm sure, as you all know,"},{"time":716333,"text":"is a pretty typical outcome,"},{"time":718423,"text":"and we never said goodbye"},{"time":719935,"text":"because we were unprepared for the end."}]},{"cues":[{"time":722990,"text":"We have a noble path to curing the disease,"},{"time":726737,"text":"patients and doctors alike,"},{"time":729067,"text":"but there doesn't seem to be"},{"time":731190,"text":"a noble path to dying."},{"time":733790,"text":"Dying is seen as failing,"},{"time":736848,"text":"and we had a heroic narrative"},{"time":739500,"text":"for fighting together,"},{"time":741593,"text":"but we didn't have a heroic narrative for letting go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":746623,"text":"So maybe we need a narrative"},{"time":750741,"text":"for acknowledging the end, and for saying goodbye,"},{"time":754217,"text":"and maybe our new story will be"},{"time":756779,"text":"about a hero's fight, and a hero's goodbye."},{"time":761385,"text":"Terence loved poetry,"},{"time":763852,"text":"and the Greek poet Constantine Cavafy"},{"time":767079,"text":"is one of my favorite poets."},{"time":769508,"text":"So I'll give you a couple lines from him."},{"time":772392,"text":"This is a poem about Mark Antony."},{"time":774608,"text":"You know Mark Antony, the conquering hero,"},{"time":777301,"text":"Cleopatra's guy?"},{"time":779166,"text":"Actually, one of Cleopatra's guys."},{"time":781703,"text":"And he's been a pretty good general."},{"time":784128,"text":"He's won all the fights,"},{"time":785188,"text":"he's eluded all the people that are out to get him,"},{"time":787643,"text":"and yet this time, finally,"},{"time":789431,"text":"he's come to the city of Alexandria"},{"time":791180,"text":"and realized he's lost."},{"time":792862,"text":"The people are leaving. They're playing instruments."},{"time":794578,"text":"They're singing."},{"time":795901,"text":"And suddenly he knows he's been defeated."},{"time":798501,"text":"And he suddenly knows"},{"time":800680,"text":"he's been deserted by the gods,"},{"time":803205,"text":"and it's time to let go."},{"time":805145,"text":"And the poet tells him what to do."},{"time":807112,"text":"He tells him how to say a noble goodbye,"},{"time":810378,"text":"a goodbye that's fit for a hero."}]},{"cues":[{"time":814225,"text":"\"As if long-prepared,"},{"time":816974,"text":"as if courageous,"},{"time":819653,"text":"as it becomes you"},{"time":822250,"text":"who were worthy of such a city,"},{"time":824422,"text":"approach the window with a firm step,"},{"time":826825,"text":"and with emotion,"},{"time":829360,"text":"but not with the entreaties"},{"time":831559,"text":"or the complaints of a coward,"},{"time":834320,"text":"as a last enjoyment,"},{"time":836291,"text":"listen to the sounds,"},{"time":838415,"text":"the exquisite instruments of the musical troops,"},{"time":841749,"text":"and bid her farewell,"},{"time":844030,"text":"the Alexandria you are losing.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":848445,"text":"That's a goodbye for a man who was larger than life,"},{"time":852135,"text":"a goodbye for a man"},{"time":854153,"text":"for whom anything,"},{"time":856127,"text":"well, almost anything,"},{"time":859235,"text":"was possible,"},{"time":861125,"text":"a goodbye for a man who kept hope alive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":864265,"text":"And isn't that what we're missing?"},{"time":866458,"text":"How can we learn that people's decisions"},{"time":868517,"text":"about their loved ones"},{"time":870027,"text":"are often based strongly, powerfully,"},{"time":873956,"text":"many times irrationally,"},{"time":876808,"text":"on the slimmest of hopes?"},{"time":879152,"text":"The overwhelming presence of hope"},{"time":882174,"text":"isn't denial."},{"time":883597,"text":"It's part of our DNA as humans,"},{"time":886417,"text":"and maybe it's time our healthcare system --"},{"time":888735,"text":"doctors, patients, insurance companies, us,"},{"time":893219,"text":"started accounting for the power of that hope."},{"time":897193,"text":"Hope isn't a bug."},{"time":899493,"text":"It's a feature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":901862,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":904357,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}